-{"id":"franken_networkx-fsft","title":"parity: Graph and DiGraph adjacency item access should return read-only atlas views","description":"Graph and DiGraph currently return raw mutable dicts from adjacency item access (G.adj['a'] and G['a']) instead of NetworkX's AtlasView wrappers. In FrankenNetworkX, assigning G['a']['x'] = {} is silently accepted and leaves the graph unchanged, while upstream NetworkX raises TypeError because the returned atlas view is read-only. Match the upstream adjacency-item contract on Graph and DiGraph, including the non-assignable AtlasView behavior.","status":"in_progress","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-21T08:41:28.720240459Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-21T08:43:08.915248323Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
