 {"id":"franken_networkx-fxbr","title":"parity: MultiGraph and MultiDiGraph edge_subgraph should preserve adjacency() mapping contract","description":"MultiGraph.edge_subgraph(...) and MultiDiGraph.edge_subgraph(...) currently collapse adjacency() to bare node iteration in FrankenNetworkX. On a single keyed edge, list(H.adjacency()) returns ['a', 'b'], while upstream NetworkX yields (node, filtered multigraph adjacency mapping) pairs that preserve keys and edge attributes. Match the upstream adjacency() contract on multigraph edge_subgraph views.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-21T09:22:41.811949314Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-22T11:34:40.698822740Z","closed_at":"2026-04-22T11:34:23.199780286Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"comments":[{"id":15,"issue_id":"franken_networkx-fxbr","author":"ubuntu","text":"Fixed in c800abf (test gate). edge_subgraph(...).adjacency() already yields (node, Mapping) where Mapping content matches nx FilterMultiInner deeply ({'b': {'k1': {'weight': 3}}} shape). Verified both MultiGraph and MultiDiGraph plus multi-key selection.","created_at":"2026-04-22T11:34:40Z"}]}
