 {"id":"franken_networkx-fyls","title":"parity: conversion live views should expose EdgeView.data() helper","description":"The top-level to_directed(...) and to_undirected(...) live views currently expose edge-view objects without NetworkX's .data() helper. In FrankenNetworkX, list(view.edges.data()) and list(view.edges.data('weight', default='NA')) raise AttributeError, while upstream NetworkX returns the expected edge-data tuples. Match the upstream EdgeView.data() helper contract on conversion live views.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-21T09:04:53.576628001Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-22T11:24:55.775213167Z","closed_at":"2026-04-22T11:24:38.973417344Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"comments":[{"id":10,"issue_id":"franken_networkx-fyls","author":"ubuntu","text":"Fixed in e32a6e6. _ConversionEdgeView.data() method delegates to view._edges(data=True) and when the first arg is a string projects to (u, v, attrs.get(name, default)) (optionally with keys). Test gate covers default / named-attr / named-attr-with-default call modes for both direction flips.","created_at":"2026-04-22T11:24:55Z"}]}
